    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "This would have significant applications to Waring's problem. Erd\\H{o}s and Graham describe this as 'unattackable by the methods at our disposal'. The case $k=2$ was resolved by Landau, who showed\\[f_{2,2}(x) \\sim \\frac{cx}{\\sqrt{\\log x}}\\]for some constant $c>0$.\n\nFor $k>2$ it is not known if $f_{k,k}(x)=o(x)$."
    },
